Art auctions worldwide totalled $12.5-billion (about R164-billion) last year, down 22% from $16.1-billion in 2015, it said. The drop was attributed to a plunge in the number of works worth more than $10-million.Top-dollar auctions last year included a painting of a haystack by Monet, Meule , which went for $81.4-million, and a Rubens masterpiece, Lot and his Daughters , sold for $58.1-million.